The lawmaker representing Sagamu State Constituency II (Makun) at Ogun State House of Assembly, Honourable Ademola Adeniran, has rehabilitated community roads in his consistency. The lawmaker also renovated Agbele Community High School, Makun, Sagamu as well as a police station outside his constituency. The rehabilitated roads include Olanle Ogunlesi street, Radelu street, Oyekan street, Isale Ojumele and Mosunmola Ashaye street while drainages on the roads were cleared, cleaned and some reconstructed. Adeniran, who had gone on a tour of secondary schools in his constituency, lamented the poor state of infrastructure in the area. He said he is renovating schools starting with Agbele Community High School as part of efforts to provide quality education and a comfortable environment for the pupils. Back Operation Amotekun with laws now, Falana tells South… You have brought joy to Kwara, Pension Board chairman tells… How billionaire Ignatius Adunukwe was killed, dismembered by… Yoruba leaders blast Miyetti Allah over opposition to… ALSO READ: Amnesty Int’l, CAN tackle Buhari over killing of Adamawa CAN chair by Boko Haram In respect of the Ayepe Road Police Station which is not located in his constituency, Adeniran said it was necessary for him to rehabilitate it because men of the Nigeria Police Force cannot efficiently carry out their functions if their welfare is not properly taken care of. He said as the people’s representative, his goal is to ensure his constituents enjoy the dividends of democracy. “What I am doing is what I promised my people during the campaign. I will not relent. “Make sure you call our attention promptly to where you see or feel that we haven’t done well enough and we won’t hesitate to do the needful. “There are so many projects to be done and executed. We are just starting, all we need is your total cooperation and prayers,” Adeniran told his constituents. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0